manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Featuring advanced aerodynamic design measures such as Flow Acceleration Channels and Noctua’s AAO frame, the NF-A6x25 is a highly optimised, premium quality quiet fan in 60x25mm size. The PWM version sports Noctua’s custom designed NE-FD1 IC for fully automatic speed control via 4-pin fan headers and comes with a Low-Noise-Adaptor to reduce the maximum speed during PWM control from 3000 to 2300rpm. Its superb running smoothness, SSO2 bearing and Noctua’s trusted premium quality make it an elite choice for the highest demands.

AAO frame Noctua's AAO (Advanced Acoustic Optimisation) frames feature integrated anti-vibration pads as well as Noctua's proprietary Stepped Inlet Design and Inner Surface Microstructures, both of which further refine the fan's performance/noise efficiency.

Reduced motor hub size Thanks to its streamlined, compact motor design, the NF-A6x25's motor hub is smaller than many conventional 6cm fans. This allows for more blade surface area and thus contributes to the NF-A6x25's superior airflow and pressure performance. SSO2 bearing The NF-A6x25 features the further optimised second generation of Noctua's renowned, time-tested SSO bearing. With SSO2, the rear magnet is placed closer to the axis to provide even better stabilisation, precision and durability. Flow Acceleration Channels The NF-A6x25 impeller features suction side Flow Acceleration Channels. By speeding up the airflow at the crucial outer blade regions, this measure reduces suction side flow separation and thus leads to better efficiency and lower vortex noise. Scope of Delivery NA-RC12 Low-Noise Adaptor (L.N.A)NA-YC1 4-pin PWM y-cableNA-EC1 30cm extension cable4x NA-AV1 anti-vibration mountsFan screws

Custom-designed PWM IC with SCD Supporting fully automatic PWM speed control, the NF-A6x25 PWM uses Noctua's custom-designed NE-FD1 PWM IC that integrates Smooth Commutation Drive (SCD) technology. By providing smoother torque impulses, SCD suppresses PWM switching noises and thus makes the fan quieter at low speeds.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Its a Noctua. Its really quiet. Doesn't move a ton of air though.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for a home-theater PC in my living room. It moves an okay amount of air for its size, temps have gone up several degrees vs. the much louder fan it replaced (also replaced two others with larger Noctuas). If you need maximum cooling, this probably isn't your best option. But if you need adequate cooling with near silence, this is the ticket.Installation was as easy as any other fan. The included cables help a lot with hooking it up to whatever pin connectors you have available. Overall, I'm happy with my purchase. Even with the reduced airflow it keeps the computer within a safe temperature range.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome little fans! Quiet 🤫 at 75% barely audible!
reviews.reviewText: I like'em! (see pics) Got two for my pc (HP P7-1010) to get more air moving in there. Also bought one of the 40x40x20 little guys to get some air coming in the side vent on my tower. These things do not move very much air. But that's OK, it's all I could really do for my tower. And who cares about the color? I think they look awesome. If you want more air movement I would get the Bgears fans. Those things are about 50% more powerful than Nactua's. I know these fans are rated at 3000RPM, the Bgears I have are rated at 5000rpm and they destroy Nactua's fans. BUT! they're louder. Not annoyingly loud, but definitely noticeable. But cmon you can't spin at 5000rpm and be silent... If you look at the picture of my side panel you'll see what I did. My pc was bought all in one at Staples back in 2011. I've upgraded everything possible. Best cpu my mobo will take(AMD Phenom II X6 1065T 95watt)(32gb RAM Kingston Hyperx Fury)(2gb EVGA Nvidia GeForce gtx 750 Ti)(two Solid State Drives by Western Digital, a 500gb, and 1TB)(Seven USB 3.0 ports (pcie card))(an Antec A30 Heatsink fan)This thing is my baby. I know it's not a custom build. But I've had it for almost 10 years and it runs fine still. I can run almost any game as of 2020 without issue. Audio and Video editing (Pro Tools & Sony Vegas Pro HD) run flawlessly. I've turned a manufacturers system into a monster. And I hope to get another 10 years out of it. But I do plan on finally building my first custom build next year. Sorry for the rambling lol I don't know why I do this on reviews lolNactua is probably the best in quality. I recommend you buy these bad boys. Or whatever size you need. Get'em!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet is an understatement.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. All I can say is: shhh … can you hear it ?So, I have this server and I was not happy with how loud it was. Server was close to my desk so I wouldn’t use it because whenever the fans will spin up it was uncomfortably loud.I kept reading about the Noctua fans being quiet so I figured I’ll replace them if I didn’t like them I could always return them.Now in my server there are 6 fans including a cpu fan cooler.I replaced only the CPU fan and I was so impressed I replaced the rest.Now, on my video the phone is right up to the server so that’s the sound you hear. At the time of the video recoding the fans were spinning fast as there was a high load on the server. However I could say the fan on my network switch is probably louder than the server.Once the server returns to regular load and the fans RPMs go down it gets even quieter.There’s even an adapter to make the fans even quieter but I didn’t use it as I don’t think they are needed.I am blown away with how quiet these fans are. Totally worth the investment. I’m happy with my server as I can now use it.If you have a computer or server right in your office or work space, do yourself a favor and get these fans. You will hear all kinds of noises that you didn’t even know where there. Lol !Five stars for Noctua !! 👍🏽

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic little fans
reviews.reviewText: Great fans that keep my PC cool. I use 2 to exhaust air out of the case and they've helped to reduce my CPU idle temps by about 5 degree. I can't speak to temps under load but they are quiet when gaming.
When retrofitting a new system into an older desktop case I had a hard time finding fans that fit. This fan fit perfectly, is quiet, and moves a decent amount of air for its size.

Pues no hay mucho que decir, es algo caro pero es simplemente un excelente ventilador, desde el empaque puedes ver la calidad de primera, con muchos extras como un cable divisor, una extensión y un cable para limitar la velocidad por si requieres que sea aún más silencioso pero dudo que a alguien le haga falta porque en verdad es super silencioso considerando que es de 3000rpm, su único "pero" es que es algo grueso.
die Lüfter sind in einen Desktop Rechner eingebaut und selbst auf voller Leistung sehr leise.Würde ich wieder kaufen, TOP >> MEINE EMPFELUNG
me ha gustado el poco ruido que producen , pero no la potencia comparativa con otros ventiladores de 12 v que rinden mejor pero generan mas ruido

Per chi non conosce questo brand beh, posso dirvi che il suo elevato prezzo ne giustifica la qualità complessiva, qualità nei materiali, ottimo flusso d'aria, buon livello sonoro, e quasi inudibile, è poi posso dirvi con certezza che vi durerà per anni, il mio modesto ed onesto consiglio è di puntare su questo brand, costa di più rispetto alla concorrenza ma vi assicuro che non ve ne pentirete.
